      <relatedmaterial id="aspace_5cd752ec7487cef6b0fc1ed4383fc645">
         <head>Associated Materials</head>
         <p>For other records concerning the history of Yale College, contact the Department of Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </relatedmaterial>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_f7adc41b703e2f4e443e810d9c673a40">
         <head>Description of the Papers</head>
         <p>The Early Yale Documents consist of correspondence, minutes, financial records, charters and official acts, inventories, and other papers documenting the founding and early history of Yale College from its early eighteenth century origins as the Collegiate School until the mid-eighteenth century, as well as some miscellaneous Yale-related material from the late eighteenth and nineteenth centuries. The collection spans the dates 1701-1889, with the bulk of the material dating from between 1701 and 1751.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <odd id="aspace_cfd67aa82a4f5113f4498d7932297c2f">
